Examples

 # \dontrun{
library("breakDown")
library("randomForest")
HR_rf_model <- randomForest(status == "fired"~., data = HR, ntree = 100)
#> Warning: The response has five or fewer unique values.  Are you sure you want to do regression?
explainer_rf  <- explain(HR_rf_model, data = HR, y = HR$status == "fired")
#> Preparation of a new explainer is initiated
#>   -> model label       :  randomForest  (  default  )
#>   -> data              :  7847  rows  6  cols 
#>   -> target variable   :  7847  values 
#>   -> predict function  :  yhat.randomForest  will be used (  default  )
#>   -> predicted values  :  numerical, min =  0.0635423 , mean =  0.3636029 , max =  0.822939  
#>   -> residual function :  difference between y and yhat (  default  )
#>   -> residuals         :  numerical, min =  -0.7839295 , mean =  0.0002304485 , max =  0.8380314  
#>   A new explainer has been created!  
mp_ex_rf <- model_performance(explainer_rf)
mp_ex_rf
#>          0%         10%         20%         30%         40%         50% 
#> -0.83803138 -0.50426434 -0.38078434 -0.25642389  0.08325914  0.12154796 
#>         60%         70%         80%         90%        100% 
#>  0.15867774  0.20969886  0.28487875  0.39629335  0.78392952 
plot(mp_ex_rf)
 # }
